Date: 22 July 1812 - Size: Small - Location: Salamanca, Western
Spain\\Scenario Briefing: The Battle of Salamanca: Securing the
Arapiles - This Getting Started scenario is designed for a French
player against a British A/I. Having only surveyed the position
during dusk, Wellington failed to include the Greater Arapile
inside his lines. The following morning, however, Marmont sent
Bonnet's entire division to secure it and Wellington, judging
it to close to his right flank, ordered the 7th Cacadores to
race to the hill and try to secure it before the French reached
it. Historically, this small scale action focussed on control
of the Greater Arapile, but the scenario gives the French player
time to push on and secure the village of Arapiles. However,
with only 8 turns, time is rather limited.\\Recommended Rules:
Default - with the following alterations - Movement Threat Disorder
and Line Movement Disruption ON
